for some nas you will need to enable a config:

gpedit.msc ->Computer Configuration->Administrative Templatrd->Network->Lanman Workstation

click on ‘Enable insicure Guest logons’

then you can map your drive or access from network as usual

to map a network drive open your PC:

on the bar of file explorer click on “Map Network Drive”

select a letter and type an IP address in the following way:

\\192.168.1.4

click on browse and choose a folder to mount

type in the nas credentials
